# policy.fi — Jesse Lastunen

> Personal academic website of Jesse Lastunen, Research Associate at UNU-WIDER (Helsinki). Focus: tax-benefit microsimulation (SOUTHMOD/EUROMOD), social policy and taxation in developing countries, poverty and inequality measurement, and the use of AI/LLMs in economics research.

## Pages

- [Home](https://policy.fi/): Biography, affiliations, and recent research.
- [Research](https://policy.fi/research/): Full list of {{ publications.length }} publications (peer-reviewed articles, book chapters, working papers, technical notes, country reports), each with abstract and citation. Machine-readable as schema.org ItemList on the page and as an Atom feed.
- [SOUTHMOD](https://policy.fi/southmod/): Resources, model documentation, an interactive model map, and a downloadable Claude Code skill for the SOUTHMOD/EUROMOD tax-benefit microsimulation models.
- [AI for Economists](https://policy.fi/ai-econ/): A curated, regularly updated library of resources for economists working with AI and LLMs — research papers, courses, coding guides (Claude Code, Cursor, Stata), AI research tools, and commentary from leading economists.

## About

Jesse Lastunen is a research associate at UNU-WIDER. He coordinates the research and technical assistance activities of the SOUTHMOD project for Vietnam, Rwanda, and Uganda, and works on tax-benefit microsimulation, social protection, and the applications of generative AI in economic research. He previously worked at organisations including RAND, OECD, and CERN, and holds a PhD in policy analysis from the Pardee RAND Graduate School.

